* ============================================================
*  PINOCCHIO AGGS ALL (single-pass multi-aggregate) PROOF
*
*  Status:  CANDIDATE / REVIEW_BEFORE_EXECUTION. READ-ONLY (no mutation).
*  Purpose: Prove `AGGS ALL <expr>` computes COUNT/SUM/AVG/MIN/MAX in ONE scan,
*           matching the four separate aggregate verbs but at ~1/4 the cost.
*
*  EXPECT (STUDENTS.GPA, 1,000,000 rows):
*    Baseline SUM/AVG/MIN/MAX = 4 full scans (~17 s each, ~68 s total).
*    AGGS ALL GPA -> one scan (~17 s), printing
*      COUNT=1000000 SUM=2.99933e+06 AVG=2.99933 MIN=2 MAX=4
*    i.e. same values, ~4x faster than running the four separately.
*
*  RUN (host):
*    powershell -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File .\dottalkpp\data\scripts\pinocchio\run_pinocchio_aggs_proof_teed.ps1
* ============================================================
SET ECHO OFF
SET TIMER ON
SET TALK OFF

SET PATH DBF DBF/pinocchio
SET PATH INDEXES INDEXES/pinocchio
SET PATH LMDB LMDB/pinocchio

SELECT 0
USE STUDENTS
SET INDEX TO STUDENTS

ECHO === A. baseline: four separate full scans over GPA ===
SUM GPA
AVG GPA
MIN GPA
MAX GPA

ECHO === B. AGGS ALL GPA -- one scan, all five values ===
AGGS ALL GPA

ECHO === C. AGGS ALL with a predicate (FOR MAJOR = CSCI; expect COUNT 90700) ===
AGGS ALL GPA FOR MAJOR = CSCI

ECHO ============================================================
ECHO AGGS ALL PROOF COMPLETE. Confirm:
ECHO   B matches A: SUM 2.99933e+06, AVG 2.99933, MIN 2, MAX 4, COUNT 1000000.
ECHO   B ELAPSED ~= ONE aggregate (~17 s), not the four combined (~68 s).
ECHO   C COUNT = 90700 (predicate path matches COUNT FOR MAJOR = CSCI).
ECHO ============================================================
